<TITLE> Six killed in Faridpur road crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Faridpur, Aug 07 (bdnews24.com)Six people died and 15 others were injured on Friday in a road crash at Mawpara in Bhanga Upazila in Faridpur, police said. Four were killed on the spot, while two others died from the wounds at Faridpur Medical College Hospital, officer in charge of Bhanga Police Station Mohammad Marfat Ullah said. The accident occurred at around 1:45pm as a bus plunged into a roadside ditch after one of its one front wheels spun off, he said. The bus was bound for Madaripur from Chandrapara of Sadarpur Upazila in Faridpur. Of the dead, Mannan Bepari, 15, Keramat Mir, 25 and Aftab Fakir, 35, were identified, Marfat Ullah said. The wounded were admitted to Faridpur Medical College Hospital, the official added. bdnews2
